WEBVTT

00:01.175 --> 00:03.220
Previously on
"Billy The Kid"...

00:04.395 --> 00:06.397
This guy Murphy, he owns
a big store in Lincoln.

00:06.528 --> 00:07.790
[Baker] They got a company
called The House,

00:07.920 --> 00:09.313
and they run it out
of Murphy's store.

00:09.444 --> 00:11.011
Well, Billy, I want to
say it is a great honor

00:11.141 --> 00:12.838
to finally meet you
in the flesh. Great honor.

00:12.969 --> 00:14.492
My partners here,

00:14.623 --> 00:17.321
-Johnny Riley, Jim Dolan.
-The Santa Fe Ring run

00:17.452 --> 00:19.019
most things
out here in the West, Billy.

00:19.149 --> 00:22.283
They are secret societies
of wealthy people.

00:22.413 --> 00:23.893
An important aspect
to your work will be

00:24.024 --> 00:26.417
to enforce
our business interests.

00:26.548 --> 00:28.419
[Riley] This fellow Tunstall,
you may have seen his new store

00:28.550 --> 00:29.812
down at the end of the street.

00:29.942 --> 00:31.901
You see, what you need
to understand here

00:32.032 --> 00:34.164
is that this is my kingdom.
I'll be damned if I'm gonna let

00:34.295 --> 00:35.905
some prick Englishman

00:36.036 --> 00:38.081
take it away from me as long
as you're around, Billy.

00:38.212 --> 00:40.301
[Jesse] We don't wanna see you
within five miles

00:40.431 --> 00:42.520
of our cattle
or our grain stores.

00:42.651 --> 00:45.567
Mr. Tunstall's got legitimate
business interests here.

00:45.697 --> 00:47.525
[Charlie] We're on the verge
of a big war.

00:47.656 --> 00:49.571
A war between Murphy
and Tunstall.

00:49.701 --> 00:51.399
Billy. I would like
to introduce you to my wife.

00:51.529 --> 00:53.053
This is Irene.

00:53.183 --> 00:55.229
It sure is nice to meet
such a handsome outlaw.

00:55.359 --> 00:56.752
See, everyone here,

00:56.882 --> 00:58.406
they want to see
what you can do with a gun.

00:58.536 --> 00:59.407
We expect you to do it.

01:03.063 --> 01:05.065
[Billy] Charlie, who is that?

01:05.195 --> 01:08.242
[Charlie] Her name is
Señorita Dulcinea del Tobosco.

01:08.372 --> 01:13.899
[speaking Spanish]

01:14.030 --> 01:17.512
These Mexican farmers think
we won't do anything

01:17.642 --> 01:18.991
about them breakin' our deals.

01:19.122 --> 01:21.037
You need to show them
that we mean business.

01:21.168 --> 01:22.778
Mr. Murphy wants you to stop
selling grain

01:22.908 --> 01:24.693
to Tunstall, right now.

01:24.823 --> 01:26.651
This is my home.
I will never leave!

01:26.782 --> 01:28.871
-[cries]
-[woman] No! No!

01:29.001 --> 01:33.093
[speaking Spanish]

01:33.223 --> 01:35.486
Sheriff Brady, he wants
to talk to Pat Garrett.

01:35.617 --> 01:38.054
What about the people here?
They're screaming for justice.

01:38.185 --> 01:39.664
Maybe he goes go away
for a while.

01:39.795 --> 01:42.624
Comes back over to your side
as a lawman.

01:42.754 --> 01:45.061
[Riley] We've heard rumors
that Tunstall has hired McSween,

01:45.192 --> 01:47.150
the lawyer that used
to work for you.

01:47.281 --> 01:50.936
I agree to meet with McSween,
it has to be in secret.

01:51.067 --> 01:52.764
A great pleasure to meet you.

01:52.895 --> 01:56.116
Unfortunately, I discovered
that Murphy himself was a crook.

01:56.246 --> 01:57.813
But after tonight,
your whole life will change.

01:57.943 --> 01:59.858
This is the time and place

01:59.989 --> 02:03.514
you have waited for
all your life.

02:12.088 --> 02:13.959
[crickets chirping]

02:14.090 --> 02:16.832
We've all heard quite
a bit about you, Billy.

02:16.962 --> 02:20.531
But the main thing from
our point of view, that is...

02:20.662 --> 02:23.969
myself and my partner,
John Tunstall,

02:24.100 --> 02:26.407
is, of course, that you work
for Mr. Murphy

02:26.537 --> 02:30.933
and The House.

02:31.063 --> 02:32.456
As you undoubtedly know,

02:32.587 --> 02:35.677
we are commercial rivals
of Mr. Murphy's.

02:35.807 --> 02:37.461
[sets glass down]

02:37.592 --> 02:38.680
Have you ever heard
of the Rings, Billy?

02:38.810 --> 02:41.552
Especially the Santa Fe Ring?

02:41.683 --> 02:43.859
As a matter of fact, I have.

02:43.989 --> 02:45.643
A journalist named Ash Upson
told me about 'em

02:45.774 --> 02:47.428
a few years ago.

02:47.558 --> 02:49.081
The Rings take different forms.

02:49.212 --> 02:50.909
Here in New Mexico,
the Rings concentrate

02:51.040 --> 02:52.781
on amassing huge landholdings

02:52.911 --> 02:55.000
through the manipulation
of Spanish land grants.

02:55.131 --> 02:57.612
That's where Murphy comes in.

02:57.742 --> 03:00.528
Precisely. He's been here long
enough to control

03:00.658 --> 03:05.010
the local Republican Party,
the election of judges,

03:05.141 --> 03:07.665
sheriffs, district attorneys,
territorial governors,

03:07.796 --> 03:09.667
you name it.

03:09.798 --> 03:12.061
And that is what Mr. Tunstall
wants to challenge.

03:12.192 --> 03:16.370
I don't see how Mr. Tunstall
could challenge any of that,

03:16.500 --> 03:17.806
even if he wanted to.

03:17.936 --> 03:21.810
Well, Mr. Tunstall is
an Englishman,

03:21.940 --> 03:23.899
an outsider.

03:24.029 --> 03:28.208
He has private wealth,
and he doesn't need the Ring.

03:28.338 --> 03:30.906
He purchased a big range,
between 3,000 and 4,000 acres,

03:31.036 --> 03:33.082
and he's been stocking it.

03:33.213 --> 03:34.823
That's what we're doing, Billy.

03:34.953 --> 03:37.608
Building a business,
so that we can deal honestly

03:37.739 --> 03:39.610
and fairly
with the farmers out here.

03:41.786 --> 03:44.615
I think Mr. Upson would
approve of that.

03:44.746 --> 03:45.877
If he's someone who cares
about justice

03:46.008 --> 03:48.445
in this part of the world,
then I'm certain

03:48.576 --> 03:50.665
he would also approve
of Mr. Tunstall.

03:50.795 --> 03:53.581
[soft music plays]

03:56.540 --> 04:00.283
[crickets chirping]

04:00.414 --> 04:02.546
"You may not believe this,
but they are training me up

04:02.677 --> 04:04.679
to be a lawman.

04:04.809 --> 04:07.595
It's the only way they can
keep me out of jail.

04:07.725 --> 04:09.988
Everybody laughs about it.

04:10.119 --> 04:12.295
But watch out, William Bonney.

04:12.426 --> 04:16.778
One day, I might be coming
for you with my new badge.

04:16.908 --> 04:22.523
Regards to all the boys,
your friend, Pat Garrett."

04:22.653 --> 04:26.353
What the hell?
Is Garrett for real?

04:26.483 --> 04:29.921
[chuckles]

04:36.972 --> 04:39.540
Hey, Jesse,
what do you think of Murphy?

04:39.670 --> 04:42.107
Oh, I don't know.
He's, uh, rich, I guess.

04:42.238 --> 04:43.805
He gets what he wants.

04:47.765 --> 04:49.811
You think he plays fair?

04:49.941 --> 04:51.203
You know, with all the farmers?

04:51.334 --> 04:52.814
Oh, you mean
the Mexican farmers?

04:52.944 --> 04:54.946
No. I mean all
the small farmers.

04:55.077 --> 04:59.037
Seems like he owns them.

04:59.168 --> 05:02.302
And this Englishman, Tunstall,
I think he's fair competition.

05:06.218 --> 05:09.396
How come you know so much
about Tunstall?

05:13.922 --> 05:16.577
You hear things.

05:21.669 --> 05:22.931
And I don't like
Murphy's henchmen.

05:26.064 --> 05:27.849
I don't like them either, Billy.

05:27.979 --> 05:30.939
But, uh, I'm not being paid
to like them.

05:34.334 --> 05:38.338
I don't see that there's much
justice in the world.

05:38.468 --> 05:42.211
I figure that's just the way
that things are,

05:42.342 --> 05:43.778
the way they've always been.

05:43.908 --> 05:47.477
What if you could change that?

05:47.608 --> 05:50.088
By doing what, exactly?

05:50.219 --> 05:53.614
I don't know. I'm just thinking.

05:53.744 --> 05:55.659
As far as I can see,
Murphy's a crook.

05:55.790 --> 05:58.053
[sighs]

05:58.183 --> 06:00.925
What if he didn't run things?

06:01.056 --> 06:02.013
[sighs]

06:02.144 --> 06:06.975
Well, then you and I...

06:07.105 --> 06:09.630
We wouldn't get paid, Billy.
Get some sleep, will you?

06:13.634 --> 06:16.637
Be careful.

06:16.767 --> 06:18.943
You don't bite the hand
that feeds you

06:19.074 --> 06:21.598
if you know what's good for you.

06:29.998 --> 06:32.696
[theme music plays]

06:45.013 --> 06:47.711
[indistinct chatter]

06:55.371 --> 06:56.546
[Murphy] Billy.

06:56.677 --> 07:00.071
[Billy] Howdy.

07:00.202 --> 07:03.553
Wet your whistle.
Bet you're thirsty.

07:15.043 --> 07:17.262
Gentlemen.

07:17.393 --> 07:20.788
Welcome to our regular meeting.

07:20.918 --> 07:24.313
Today we want to discuss some
new business we have for you.

07:24.444 --> 07:27.708
As you know, some of
the farmers down on the Bonito

07:27.838 --> 07:31.059
and the Hondo have broken
their contracts with us,

07:31.189 --> 07:34.802
therefore forfeiting
their rights to their farms.

07:34.932 --> 07:38.240
Now, I've just returned from
a business trip to Santa Fe,

07:38.370 --> 07:40.851
and I found a number
of investors both willing

07:40.982 --> 07:43.724
and eager to buy
those properties.

07:43.854 --> 07:49.425
These current occupiers,
now in default,

07:49.556 --> 07:52.080
they need to be
driven off the farms.

07:52.210 --> 07:56.345
So, here's a list of them
and where you can find them.

07:56.476 --> 07:58.826
Don't use unnecessary force.

07:58.956 --> 08:00.044
But on the other hand,

08:00.175 --> 08:02.394
we do expect you
to do your jobs.

08:02.525 --> 08:04.962
This is a perfectly legal
operation.

08:05.093 --> 08:07.835
These people have no right
to remain on our land.

08:07.965 --> 08:09.880
[Dolan] Boys, uh...

08:10.011 --> 08:13.057
Well, you decide how you're
going to handle it, right?

08:13.188 --> 08:14.929
It's nothing to us.

08:15.059 --> 08:18.106
Now, Major Murphy's throwing
a party this evening,

08:18.236 --> 08:20.195
and he'd like you all to attend.

08:20.325 --> 08:22.937
It's a request he's made.

08:23.067 --> 08:25.330
I hope you all find yourselves
able to oblige.

08:25.461 --> 08:27.115
[Jesse] Not gonna miss out
on a party, are we boys?

08:27.245 --> 08:28.682
[laughing]

08:28.812 --> 08:33.077
Of course you don't.

08:33.208 --> 08:37.168
And how about you, Billy?

08:37.299 --> 08:39.867
Sticking around, are ya?

08:39.997 --> 08:42.652
[somber music plays]

08:49.877 --> 08:52.532
[sighs]

08:56.318 --> 08:59.060
[indistinct chatter]

09:03.934 --> 09:06.023
[fiddle playing in distance]

09:06.154 --> 09:11.159
[laughter]

09:11.289 --> 09:13.204
[indistinct chatter continues]

09:13.335 --> 09:16.643
[playing ballad]

09:16.773 --> 09:19.559
♪♪♪

09:24.215 --> 09:26.870
[indistinct chatter continues]

09:27.001 --> 09:29.830
♪♪♪

09:39.143 --> 09:43.452
♪♪♪

09:43.583 --> 09:48.718
[distorted conversations]

09:48.849 --> 09:54.942
♪♪♪

09:55.072 --> 09:58.380
[distorted conversations
continue]

09:58.510 --> 10:01.905
♪♪♪

10:02.036 --> 10:07.041
[indistinct conversations
continue]

10:07.171 --> 10:08.956
Jesse.

10:09.086 --> 10:10.087
Excuse us.

10:10.218 --> 10:17.094
♪♪♪

10:17.225 --> 10:19.183
What's up, Billy?

10:19.314 --> 10:21.751
When do you plan to drive
those farmers out?

10:21.882 --> 10:24.101
Tomorrow. Why?

10:24.232 --> 10:24.841
I won't be going with you.

10:28.976 --> 10:31.108
-Why the hell not?
-I don't want to.

10:31.239 --> 10:33.067
You do it.

10:33.197 --> 10:38.899
[indistinct conversations
continue]

10:39.029 --> 10:40.030
Okay.

10:44.382 --> 10:46.950
Hello there, Billy.

10:47.081 --> 10:48.038
Mrs. Riley.

10:48.169 --> 10:50.171
I wanted to see you.

10:50.301 --> 10:53.000
I want to talk to you.
I need to.

10:53.130 --> 10:55.132
Uh, maybe now's
not a good time.

10:55.263 --> 10:59.920
Oh, no. Definitely now.
I have something to say.

11:00.050 --> 11:02.096
Get me another drink, will you?

11:02.226 --> 11:06.796
Sure.

11:09.277 --> 11:10.800
Gracias.

11:14.499 --> 11:17.328
What did you want to say?

11:17.459 --> 11:21.202
I want to tell you
about my husband.

11:21.332 --> 11:24.118
What about your husband?

11:24.248 --> 11:26.990
I...

11:27.121 --> 11:29.123
I hate him.

11:29.253 --> 11:33.301
He treats me so bad.
You can't even imagine.

11:33.431 --> 11:35.216
Maybe this isn't the place
to talk about this.

11:35.346 --> 11:40.700
No.
Light my cigarette, will ya?

11:55.976 --> 11:58.718
Thank you.

11:58.848 --> 12:02.373
You know, you're very
good-looking, Billy.

12:02.504 --> 12:04.245
Can we go somewhere?
I like you.

12:07.117 --> 12:09.554
I don't think
that's a good idea.

12:09.685 --> 12:14.951
Please. Please, Billy.

12:15.082 --> 12:21.175
I told you I hate him.
I have to get away.

12:21.305 --> 12:24.091
No.

12:24.221 --> 12:26.006
I'm sorry, Mrs. Riley.

12:29.531 --> 12:33.274
Never mind.
It's not your fault.

12:46.287 --> 12:47.767
[chuckles]

12:50.378 --> 12:53.076
[suspenseful music plays]

12:58.168 --> 13:02.085
♪♪♪

13:02.216 --> 13:04.914
[indistinct chatter]

13:13.009 --> 13:13.923
[door slams]

13:14.054 --> 13:16.056
Hey!

13:16.186 --> 13:19.581
[grunting] Oh!

13:19.711 --> 13:21.104
You fucking lousy
fucking bitch.

13:21.235 --> 13:22.714
What do you mean?

13:22.845 --> 13:25.282
I saw you in there...
with Billy.

13:25.413 --> 13:27.415
I know what you were doing.

13:27.545 --> 13:28.720
You was trying to get him
to fuck you,

13:28.851 --> 13:30.374
because you're
a little fucking whore.

13:30.505 --> 13:32.507
I'm tired. I want to sleep.

13:32.637 --> 13:34.683
I've had enough of you.
Do you understand?

13:34.814 --> 13:36.990
You're a fucking embarrassment.

13:37.120 --> 13:38.556
You're always out there
in heat.

13:38.687 --> 13:40.471
It's fucking disgusting
and I've had e-fucking-nough!

13:40.602 --> 13:43.953
So have I!
I've had enough of you!

13:44.084 --> 13:47.174
I hate you!

13:47.304 --> 13:49.437
[dramatic music plays]

13:49.567 --> 13:52.309
Aah!

13:52.440 --> 13:55.443
♪♪♪

13:58.011 --> 14:01.318
[panting]

14:01.449 --> 14:05.105
[indistinct chatter]

14:05.235 --> 14:06.584
[man] She's dead!

14:06.715 --> 14:10.110
[panting]

14:10.240 --> 14:11.589
What did you do?

14:11.720 --> 14:14.244
She shot me.
She tried to kill me!

14:14.375 --> 14:16.116
Now, you get me
some fucking help!

14:16.246 --> 14:18.335
Hey, hey, hey!
What the hell is happening?

14:18.466 --> 14:19.684
Your friend killed his wife.

14:19.815 --> 14:22.252
She shot me! Look at me!

14:22.383 --> 14:25.212
Okay, okay, okay.
Just...Billy.

14:25.342 --> 14:26.953
Billy, put it down, all right?

14:30.739 --> 14:33.133
Hey, go fetch the doctor, huh?

14:33.263 --> 14:34.743
Hey, come on. Come on.
Let's go inside.

14:34.874 --> 14:36.092
I'll help you, all right?

14:36.223 --> 14:37.485
Come on.

14:37.615 --> 14:40.314
-Oh, fuck.
-We need a fucking Sheriff!

14:40.444 --> 14:41.532
Just go!

14:41.663 --> 14:44.144
Come on. Come on.

14:44.274 --> 14:47.103
♪♪♪

15:07.558 --> 15:09.343
[Billy] Is Tunstall back yet?

15:09.473 --> 15:10.692
[Charlie] Sure is.

15:10.822 --> 15:12.389
He wants to meet you up
at my farm.

15:12.520 --> 15:17.046
All right.

15:18.482 --> 15:20.658
[tongue clicks]

15:20.789 --> 15:23.139
Hah! Hah!

15:27.491 --> 15:29.232
Whoa.

15:29.363 --> 15:31.408
[Jesse] Okay.

15:31.539 --> 15:33.062
Let's see if we can't chase
these fellas outta here.

15:33.193 --> 15:34.281
Yeah.

15:34.411 --> 15:35.238
[Jesse] Let's go, boys.

15:35.369 --> 15:38.328
-Yup, yup!
-Hyah! Hyah!

15:41.853 --> 15:44.247
-[man] Yup!
-[Olinger] Let's go, boys!

15:44.378 --> 15:48.295
[menacing music plays]

15:48.425 --> 15:51.167
Get back.

15:51.298 --> 15:52.952
[Olinger] Let's go, boys!

16:00.220 --> 16:05.138
♪♪♪

16:06.661 --> 16:08.358
What the hell you boys up to?

16:08.489 --> 16:10.404
You gotta clear outta here!

16:10.534 --> 16:13.233
The hell I will.

16:13.363 --> 16:15.452
Now, you get off my property!
You hear?

16:15.583 --> 16:17.324
[groaning, horses whinnies]

16:17.454 --> 16:20.109
[gunshot]

16:34.297 --> 16:37.866
[gunshots continue]

16:37.997 --> 16:40.260
We don't wanna kill ya!

16:40.390 --> 16:42.436
Just come out
and give yourselves up!

16:42.566 --> 16:44.742
-[man] This is our property!
-[Baker] Not your land anymore!

16:44.873 --> 16:46.875
[man] You got no right
being here!

16:47.006 --> 16:48.268
We got every right to be here!

16:52.489 --> 16:53.925
[pants]

16:54.056 --> 16:56.798
[lowered voice]
Get in behind them.

16:56.928 --> 16:58.669
-You got us?
-Get around behind them.

16:58.800 --> 17:01.020
-Yeah.
-We got you.

17:02.891 --> 17:04.458
[gasps]

17:04.588 --> 17:08.331
♪♪♪

17:12.596 --> 17:13.597
-[cocks gun]
-[Baker] Come on out, now.

17:13.728 --> 17:15.686
Drop your guns.
We ain't gonna kill you.

17:15.817 --> 17:17.340
[man] Me and my family
have worked this land

17:17.471 --> 17:19.473
close on 20 years!

17:19.603 --> 17:22.650
I'm not giving it
to people like you!

17:22.780 --> 17:24.869
[Baker] You cannot fight
the future, boy!

17:25.000 --> 17:27.742
Just come on out here!

17:27.872 --> 17:30.179
[grunts]

17:30.310 --> 17:31.224
Come on!

17:34.270 --> 17:36.664
♪♪♪

17:36.794 --> 17:40.233
[groaning]

17:40.363 --> 17:43.236
-Come here, sweetheart.
-[groans]

17:43.366 --> 17:44.715
Come on!

17:47.370 --> 17:50.808
[woman screaming]

17:50.939 --> 17:51.896
[groans]

17:52.027 --> 17:55.509
[woman] Help! Help me, somebody!

17:55.639 --> 17:56.858
No!

17:56.988 --> 18:00.209
[sobbing] No!

18:00.340 --> 18:02.864
Stop, please!

18:02.994 --> 18:06.346
[screaming]

18:06.476 --> 18:07.912
[groans]

18:08.043 --> 18:10.350
[woman] No! [sobbing]

18:10.480 --> 18:13.788
[woman screaming]

18:13.918 --> 18:17.618
[woman] No, please, stop!

18:17.748 --> 18:20.969
[screaming, sobbing]

18:21.100 --> 18:22.710
[woman] No, please! Don't!

18:22.840 --> 18:23.841
[screaming]

18:23.972 --> 18:24.842
[gunshot]

18:28.324 --> 18:32.633
♪♪♪

18:32.763 --> 18:35.505
[breathing deeply]

18:48.431 --> 18:50.868
[horse blusters]

18:50.999 --> 18:53.784
Hola,Billy.

18:53.915 --> 18:58.615
Hola,Manuela.

19:02.924 --> 19:08.582
[insects chirping]

19:08.712 --> 19:10.410
[horse nickers]

19:14.501 --> 19:17.199
[galloping in distance]

19:22.117 --> 19:24.902
[suspenseful music plays]

19:25.033 --> 19:27.644
♪♪♪

19:27.775 --> 19:30.256
Hyah! Hyah! Hyah!

19:30.386 --> 19:32.780
♪♪♪

19:32.910 --> 19:34.651
Gracias.

19:54.628 --> 19:57.500
I'm so very glad
to meet you, Billy.

19:57.631 --> 19:58.980
My name's John Tunstall.

20:08.076 --> 20:10.296
[panting]

20:10.426 --> 20:11.993
Hyah, hyah!

20:12.123 --> 20:13.821
Get in the barn.

20:13.951 --> 20:15.605
Get in the barn! Get back! Go!

20:17.694 --> 20:19.435
Run!

20:19.566 --> 20:23.439
John!

20:23.570 --> 20:26.007
Get in the house!
Get in the house!

20:27.922 --> 20:29.576
No!

20:29.706 --> 20:30.707
-No!
-[horse whinnies]

20:30.838 --> 20:33.449
John! Come on!

20:33.580 --> 20:34.624
No!

20:34.755 --> 20:37.323
[screaming]

20:37.453 --> 20:39.499
[gunshots]

20:39.629 --> 20:42.328
[grunts]

20:42.458 --> 20:46.636
[sobbing]

20:46.767 --> 20:49.987
[gunshots]

20:50.118 --> 20:52.425
[woman] No, leave us! Leave us!

20:52.555 --> 20:54.688
No, John, no!

20:54.818 --> 20:56.080
[sobbing]

20:56.211 --> 20:57.908
You gotta clear off this land!

20:58.039 --> 21:01.869
You killed my husband!

21:01.999 --> 21:03.044
[sobbing]

21:03.174 --> 21:04.915
My sons!

21:05.046 --> 21:07.483
My poor daughter!

21:07.614 --> 21:09.790
We never did anything wrong!

21:09.920 --> 21:12.053
You got
till the end of the day!

21:12.183 --> 21:19.669
No! No! [sobbing]

21:19.800 --> 21:25.153
[Jesse] Come on, boys! Yah!

21:25.284 --> 21:29.505
Your lawyer, Mr. McSween,
told me about your ambitions.

21:29.636 --> 21:31.986
Want to start a business
to rival The House.

21:32.116 --> 21:34.902
Well, I realize that a lot
of what goes on here,

21:35.032 --> 21:39.776
in Lincoln County, especially,
is rather up for grabs.

21:39.907 --> 21:42.779
And, frankly, I plan to grab
every bit of land I can,

21:42.910 --> 21:45.216
for as little as possible.

21:45.347 --> 21:47.131
Can't fault you for that,
Mr. Tunstall.

21:47.262 --> 21:50.265
Please, call me John.

21:50.396 --> 21:54.487
And, if I may,
I shall call you Billy.

21:54.617 --> 21:57.664
[sets glass down]

21:57.794 --> 21:59.622
That's all right by me.

21:59.753 --> 22:01.885
The fact is, Billy,
John is prepared

22:02.016 --> 22:04.627
to pay us farmers fairly,
whatever we produce.

22:04.758 --> 22:06.629
That's true.

22:06.760 --> 22:08.588
I think Murphy is exploiting
his position here,

22:08.718 --> 22:09.937
forcing the farmers into debt,

22:10.067 --> 22:11.721
and then forcing them
off their lands.

22:11.852 --> 22:13.680
Now, I don't intend to do that.

22:13.810 --> 22:15.812
But John and all of us
are aware that Murphy

22:15.943 --> 22:18.467
isn't gonna let go of
his position without a fight.

22:18.598 --> 22:20.339
He's got a lot of guns.

22:26.997 --> 22:30.000
I noticed your lawyer,
McSween...

22:30.131 --> 22:32.786
a very religious man.

22:32.916 --> 22:35.005
He is.

22:35.136 --> 22:40.010
He has his faith,
and he has his principles.

22:40.141 --> 22:42.012
He's a very unusual man
for around here.

22:42.143 --> 22:47.061
What about you, John?

22:47.191 --> 22:48.628
What are your principles?

22:54.721 --> 22:57.288
"To thine own self be true.

22:57.419 --> 23:01.858
And it must follow
as night the day."

23:01.989 --> 23:03.599
[men] Hyah, hyah!

23:03.730 --> 23:05.601
"Thou cannot be false
to any man."

23:05.732 --> 23:07.081
[Baker] Come on, come on!

23:07.211 --> 23:08.865
It's from Shakespeare.

23:08.996 --> 23:11.215
♪♪♪

23:11.346 --> 23:12.826
Come on, come on now!

23:12.956 --> 23:14.523
Come on!

23:14.654 --> 23:18.048
[yelping, laughing]

23:18.179 --> 23:22.183
[man] Hyah! Hyah!

23:22.313 --> 23:24.054
What are you doing
on this land?

23:24.185 --> 23:26.143
This is our land.

23:26.274 --> 23:28.058
Oh, no, no.

23:28.189 --> 23:30.931
Not anymore it's not.

23:31.061 --> 23:33.194
[shouts indistinctly]

23:33.324 --> 23:36.545
-Whoo!
-[horse whinnies]

23:36.676 --> 23:41.245
Billy...

23:41.376 --> 23:43.465
I would regard it as
a great honor if you would

23:43.596 --> 23:46.860
consider leaving Murphy's
employment and joining mine.

23:46.990 --> 23:50.037
I realize I'm asking you
a great deal.

23:50.167 --> 23:52.735
You must be working
with good friends,

23:52.866 --> 23:54.955
being very well remunerated
by The House,

23:55.085 --> 23:58.828
and I doubt I can offer you
as much.

23:58.959 --> 24:01.918
On the other hand, I think
I canoffer you something

24:02.049 --> 24:06.227
that is perhaps more important
than money.

24:06.357 --> 24:09.186
I want to run
a legitimate business.

24:09.317 --> 24:13.756
I'm not a crook, like Murphy.

24:13.887 --> 24:18.152
Now, I know in certain places
you're wanted for murder,

24:18.282 --> 24:22.722
and in those places,
there's a bounty on your head.

24:22.852 --> 24:28.379
Even so, I am willing
and happy to take you on.

24:28.510 --> 24:30.947
If you go straight,
and you work hard,

24:31.078 --> 24:34.342
both of which I believe
you're very capable of,

24:34.473 --> 24:37.650
in due course, I will petition
the governor on your behalf.

24:41.262 --> 24:45.179
A very big offer to make,
Mr. Tunstall...

24:45.309 --> 24:47.747
especially for someone
you don't know from Adam.

24:47.877 --> 24:50.053
I know.

24:50.184 --> 24:53.753
I believe,
and Charlie here also believes,

24:53.883 --> 24:56.886
that you are trustworthy...

24:57.017 --> 24:57.974
and honest.

25:00.760 --> 25:05.939
Whatever your reputation.

25:06.069 --> 25:08.158
If I switch sides,
there'll be consequences.

25:10.552 --> 25:14.208
I just needed to say
what I've said.

25:14.338 --> 25:17.080
This is a big undertaking.

25:17.211 --> 25:19.126
I would really like you
to be a part of it.

25:23.913 --> 25:27.177
[laughter]

25:29.005 --> 25:30.267
[horse blusters]

25:30.398 --> 25:32.139
Hey there.

25:32.269 --> 25:35.011
How much for one
of your melons?

25:35.142 --> 25:37.971
It's all right.
We ain't gonna hurt ya.

25:38.101 --> 25:40.408
[Beckwith] Come on.
Toss one over here.

25:40.539 --> 25:42.018
Olinger, give me
that drink, man.

25:42.149 --> 25:44.717
[Baker] Here, here, here.

25:44.847 --> 25:46.719
Oh, yeah.

25:47.981 --> 25:52.202
[laughter]

25:52.333 --> 25:53.856
[Jesse] Oh! Uh-oh.

25:53.987 --> 25:55.554
Whoo!

25:55.684 --> 25:57.773
Come on, boy, run.
You gotta go faster than that.

25:57.904 --> 25:59.645
-He's running.
-Look at that.

25:59.775 --> 26:02.865
[laughter]

26:02.996 --> 26:04.171
[hammer clicks]

26:04.301 --> 26:06.869
[Beckwith] Run, boy!

26:07.000 --> 26:11.047
♪♪♪

26:11.178 --> 26:13.789
[laughter]

26:20.970 --> 26:22.885
[horse blusters]

26:27.368 --> 26:28.717
[driver] Whoa.

26:41.425 --> 26:43.471
This is cold-blooded murder.

26:43.602 --> 26:46.909
I'll send someone out to
Sheriff Brady to report it.

26:47.040 --> 26:49.259
We know exactly
who's behind this.

26:49.390 --> 26:52.219
No doubt about it.

26:52.349 --> 26:55.352
Seems like Murphy's
gotten desperate.

26:55.483 --> 26:56.310
[Tunstall]
You think Sheriff Brady

26:56.440 --> 26:57.746
will do anything about this?

26:57.877 --> 27:01.924
I can't say.

27:02.055 --> 27:03.839
He's an honored war veteran
and a good sheriff,

27:03.970 --> 27:04.884
all things considered.

27:05.014 --> 27:09.366
But?

27:09.497 --> 27:15.416
But he's also had a long-time
friendship with Major Murphy.

27:15.546 --> 27:16.330
I think that answers
my question.

27:16.460 --> 27:17.287
[sighs]

27:22.249 --> 27:24.773
I'm so sorry, Mrs. Hudgens.

27:27.689 --> 27:32.302
I will get their bodies
back to town.

27:32.433 --> 27:34.217
You and your daughter can
come over to my house

27:34.348 --> 27:36.437
and stay with me until
the funerals if it suits you.

27:36.567 --> 27:40.789
[voice breaking]
Thank you, Mr. Tunstall.

27:40.920 --> 27:43.270
[horse galloping]

27:43.400 --> 27:45.228
What is it?

27:45.359 --> 27:47.927
You all better come over
to Jose Chavez's farm.

27:48.057 --> 27:49.276
More killings?

27:49.406 --> 27:51.670
Afraid so.

27:53.976 --> 27:55.195
[sighs]

27:55.325 --> 27:56.805
[indistinct chatter, laughter]

27:59.286 --> 28:01.288
[Jesse] Hey, Billy boy!

28:01.418 --> 28:03.464
Hey, hey!

28:03.594 --> 28:06.032
Missed all the fun today,
Billy.

28:06.162 --> 28:07.468
[Billy] Yeah, what kind of fun?

28:07.598 --> 28:09.905
Well, we did what Mr. Murphy
wanted us to do.

28:10.036 --> 28:12.081
We drove those farmers off
their property.

28:12.212 --> 28:15.171
-Billy!
-Hell, yeah, we did.

28:15.302 --> 28:18.218
You kill any of them?

28:18.348 --> 28:22.004
What do you think?
'Course we did.

28:22.135 --> 28:24.224
Some of those fuckers
fired back at us.

28:24.354 --> 28:25.965
Shot and killed Arly.

28:28.054 --> 28:30.839
How many did you kill?

28:30.970 --> 28:33.320
Oh, I don't know.

28:33.450 --> 28:36.236
Now, why do you care
about those farmers so? Huh?

28:36.366 --> 28:39.935
Are you gonna cry now?
Is that it?

28:40.066 --> 28:41.632
-[laughter]
-Glad you had fun.

28:41.763 --> 28:44.331
Oh, yeah, it was real fun,
Billy.

28:44.461 --> 28:45.854
It's what we get paid for.

28:45.985 --> 28:47.203
-Whoo!
-[laughter]

28:47.334 --> 28:49.553
Bob Olinger.

28:49.684 --> 28:51.991
Dirty, dirty bastard.

28:52.121 --> 28:53.383
[man] What the hell you guys
doing here?

28:53.514 --> 28:55.037
What are you doing here?
What the hell you doing here?

28:55.168 --> 28:57.039
[indistinct chatter]

28:57.170 --> 28:59.041
♪♪♪

28:59.172 --> 29:00.869
[horse whinnies]

29:12.533 --> 29:15.101
[man] Howdy, Sheriff.

29:23.065 --> 29:24.197
[horse blusters]

29:24.327 --> 29:25.981
Gentlemen.

29:26.112 --> 29:29.463
Sheriff.

29:29.593 --> 29:31.378
How's that arm of yours, Jim?

29:31.508 --> 29:33.380
Pretty good.
Thank you, Sheriff.

29:33.510 --> 29:35.512
It's a shame when a woman
like that goes off the rails.

29:42.519 --> 29:44.347
As Sheriff of Lincoln County,

29:44.478 --> 29:46.349
I want to open this inquiry
into the deaths

29:46.480 --> 29:51.354
of 14 persons by firearms
in this county.

29:51.485 --> 29:53.922
Who wants to speak to
the violators of these crimes?

29:54.053 --> 29:56.055
Well, I do, Sheriff.

29:56.185 --> 29:58.057
I'm a lawyer acting
for Mr. John Tunstall,

29:58.187 --> 30:00.407
and we have already registered
that Major Murphy

30:00.537 --> 30:03.018
has openly declared war
on my client.

30:03.149 --> 30:04.759
Sheriff, you don't have
to listen

30:04.890 --> 30:07.109
to this Santa Fe law-speak.
All right?

30:07.240 --> 30:09.459
We don't need lawyers
in Lincoln County.

30:09.590 --> 30:11.200
We're perfectly capable
of sorting out our difficulties

30:11.331 --> 30:13.159
all by ourselves.

30:13.289 --> 30:15.248
Mr. Dolan, the law has to be
respected at all times.

30:15.378 --> 30:18.468
No one can run roughshod
over it.

30:18.599 --> 30:20.993
Do you have any idea why
these people were killed?

30:21.123 --> 30:23.647
No, sir.

30:23.778 --> 30:25.606
These killings,
they were nothing to do

30:25.736 --> 30:27.608
with The House
or Mr. Murphy personally.

30:27.738 --> 30:29.610
He was just as shocked
as everyone else

30:29.740 --> 30:31.568
to hear about them.

30:31.699 --> 30:33.527
Major Murphy is
an interested party.

30:33.657 --> 30:35.616
It's obvious that he wanted
these farmers and their families

30:35.746 --> 30:37.531
run off the land,
one way or another.

30:37.661 --> 30:40.708
They were random shootings
by persons unknown.

30:40.839 --> 30:43.624
Probably some criminal gang just
passing through Lincoln County.

30:43.754 --> 30:46.453
There is indeed a criminal gang
operating inside Lincoln County,

30:46.583 --> 30:48.194
and it's our contention that
The House pays them

30:48.324 --> 30:49.456
for their services.

30:49.586 --> 30:52.285
You got any proof there,
Mr. McSween?

30:52.415 --> 30:54.896
Hmm?

30:55.027 --> 30:55.984
Not yet.

30:56.115 --> 30:58.291
[scoffs] Yeah.

30:58.421 --> 30:59.988
Do you think you should get
Colonel Dudley up at the fort

31:00.119 --> 31:01.337
involved in this, Sheriff?

31:01.468 --> 31:03.557
No, I do not.

31:03.687 --> 31:06.081
This is a civil matter,
and before I do anything else,

31:06.212 --> 31:07.517
my deputies and I
will make inquiries

31:07.648 --> 31:11.086
to determine the facts.

31:11.217 --> 31:12.566
Thank you for your time,
gentlemen.

31:12.696 --> 31:17.919
This meeting is concluded.

31:18.050 --> 31:19.399
[sighs]

31:23.577 --> 31:30.236
My good friend,
Jose Chavez y Chavez...

31:30.366 --> 31:34.370
they killed his sons.

31:34.501 --> 31:37.112
He is so sad.

31:37.243 --> 31:41.377
Está muy desesperado.

31:41.508 --> 31:44.685
His whole family...gone.

31:47.514 --> 31:50.169
I understand, Señor Baca.

31:50.299 --> 31:52.693
It's a terrible crime.
Terrible crime.

32:00.875 --> 32:02.268
We're friends, right?

32:02.398 --> 32:04.487
Claro.

32:04.618 --> 32:06.359
I've always told you
the truth, yes?

32:06.489 --> 32:08.230
Sí.

32:08.361 --> 32:11.581
Men who killed Chavez y Chavez's
sons were hired

32:11.712 --> 32:15.107
by the Englishman,
John Tunstall.

32:15.237 --> 32:16.935
Do you know who that is?

32:17.065 --> 32:19.459
Sí,I know who he is,
but I never thought--

32:19.589 --> 32:22.723
Now, he's trying to drive me
out of business.

32:22.853 --> 32:25.987
Which is...
It's gonna affect you.

32:26.118 --> 32:28.555
Because you and me, we have
a business together, no?

32:28.685 --> 32:30.731
Sí.

32:30.861 --> 32:33.734
You want to keep it
that way, yes?

32:33.864 --> 32:35.997
Sí.

32:36.128 --> 32:39.566
So we don't want any trouble
with any of your people.

32:39.696 --> 32:42.612
No trouble.

32:42.743 --> 32:44.788
So, what I want you to do is,
I want you to tell everyone

32:44.919 --> 32:46.921
that those shootings had
nothing to do with me,

32:47.052 --> 32:52.492
they had everything to do
with the Englishman.

32:52.622 --> 32:54.320
Will you do that for me?

32:54.450 --> 32:59.586
[suspenseful music plays]

32:59.716 --> 33:02.197
Sí.

33:02.328 --> 33:03.633
I don't want any trouble.

33:08.725 --> 33:12.294
Good.

33:12.425 --> 33:15.645
We'll send flowers
to the funeral.

33:15.776 --> 33:18.779
Those poor boys.

33:18.909 --> 33:20.433
Why do things have to be like
this these days, my old friend?

33:20.563 --> 33:22.217
Why?

33:22.348 --> 33:27.179
I agree. [clears throat]

33:27.309 --> 33:32.140
Things used to be
so peaceful here.

33:32.271 --> 33:34.142
This was a beautiful place.

33:41.541 --> 33:43.586
And it'll be
a beautiful place again.

33:43.717 --> 33:47.503
Believe me, my friend.

33:47.634 --> 33:49.418
Soon as we get rid
of that Englishman.

34:01.343 --> 34:03.215
[crickets chirping]

34:03.345 --> 34:06.174
♪♪♪

34:23.800 --> 34:27.674
[Paddy] Do you see those stars
up there, Billy?

34:27.804 --> 34:34.550
You are just like one
of those stars.

34:34.681 --> 34:40.904
You can burn so bright.

34:41.035 --> 34:46.345
Those are bright,
burning stars up there.

34:51.089 --> 34:54.266
They reflect the light...

34:54.396 --> 34:57.443
that's in you.

35:11.370 --> 35:14.112
[somber music plays]

35:25.732 --> 35:27.125
Just a minute.

35:39.659 --> 35:41.878
Easy, boy.

35:43.706 --> 35:44.751
[horse nickers]

35:47.623 --> 35:48.798
[man] Adios.

35:48.929 --> 35:50.452
Buenas noches.

35:50.583 --> 35:52.672
-Señoritadel Tobosco.
-[door closes]

35:55.457 --> 35:57.285
Perdón, Señorita.

36:00.462 --> 36:01.681
Wait a minute.

36:06.686 --> 36:07.904
Who are you?

36:08.035 --> 36:12.082
I'm Billy.

36:12.213 --> 36:13.954
I just wanted
to introduce myself.

36:14.084 --> 36:15.869
Well, that is not
a very good reason

36:15.999 --> 36:18.567
to ambush someone in the street.

36:18.698 --> 36:20.047
Do you have another motive?

36:20.178 --> 36:23.746
I'd like to see you again.

36:23.877 --> 36:25.705
Why?

36:25.835 --> 36:29.361
Step away, friend.
You're annoying the Señorita.

36:43.984 --> 36:45.942
Gracias, Señorita.

36:46.073 --> 36:48.858
Did you imagine I had no idea
of what happens in this town?

36:55.517 --> 36:59.347
Shame on you.

37:09.139 --> 37:11.838
You may see me again.

37:11.968 --> 37:13.753
If you wish.

37:13.883 --> 37:16.321
[intriguing music plays]

37:16.451 --> 37:19.715
♪♪♪

37:28.289 --> 37:30.900
We're meeting
at McSween's tomorrow.

37:31.031 --> 37:34.904
Are you with us?

37:35.035 --> 37:38.517
[insects, birds chirping]

37:43.913 --> 37:49.919
[sighs] Mr. Tunstall.
Gentlemen.

37:50.050 --> 37:51.660
There is little doubt
we are now as good

37:51.791 --> 37:55.011
as at war with Major Murphy
and The House.

37:55.142 --> 37:57.013
So far, in this
commercial conflict,

37:57.144 --> 37:58.928
the law has not been
on our side.

37:59.059 --> 38:00.103
I think we all know
the reason for that.

38:00.234 --> 38:03.585
Yes. The Rings.

38:03.716 --> 38:05.848
Murphy has powerful friends
in important places,

38:05.979 --> 38:08.677
but that doesn't mean
he isn't vulnerable.

38:08.808 --> 38:10.810
His business is failing,
partly through our own efforts.

38:10.940 --> 38:12.812
It's really a house of cards.

38:12.942 --> 38:14.030
You take away a couple
of the bottom cards,

38:14.161 --> 38:15.902
the whole house starts to fall.

38:16.032 --> 38:18.774
We can take them to court
for their illegal activities.

38:18.905 --> 38:20.950
The way they cheat the army
with their beef rations,

38:21.081 --> 38:23.562
their tyrannical attitude
to their farmers.

38:23.692 --> 38:25.607
I'm already preparing
the papers,

38:25.738 --> 38:28.393
but there's no point
going to court in Santa Fe.

38:28.523 --> 38:32.658
The head of the Santa Fe Ring
is a man called Thomas Catron,

38:32.788 --> 38:35.530
and he turns out to be
a good friend of Major Murphy.

38:35.661 --> 38:39.012
Meanwhile, The House is
hiring more guns.

38:39.142 --> 38:41.057
I'm afraid that's true.

38:41.188 --> 38:43.146
I've heard of the recruitment
of another six sharp-shooters,

38:43.277 --> 38:46.019
joining those already
in Murphy's employ.

38:46.149 --> 38:49.805
This war is never going to be
won just in the courts.

38:52.025 --> 38:56.159
No.

38:56.290 --> 38:59.815
The truth is,
all our lives are at risk.

38:59.946 --> 39:02.557
If we are to fight this war,

39:02.688 --> 39:04.690
more blood will be spilled.

39:04.820 --> 39:09.129
We'll hire more guns ourselves.

39:09.259 --> 39:12.785
But we'll need an advantage
to survive this.

39:12.915 --> 39:14.743
[door creaks]

39:21.315 --> 39:24.100
[dramatic music plays]

39:24.231 --> 39:27.016
♪♪♪

39:33.153 --> 39:34.720
Mr. Tunstall.

39:37.157 --> 39:39.028
I'm ready to go to work.

39:42.641 --> 39:45.426
♪♪♪

39:57.917 --> 39:59.875
[Jesse] Where you been, Billy?

40:02.008 --> 40:03.618
Around.

40:03.749 --> 40:05.490
Yeah. And where's that?

40:05.620 --> 40:07.143
[laughter]

40:07.274 --> 40:09.929
I came to tell you something.

40:13.498 --> 40:15.891
I'm quitting
Major Murphy's payroll.

40:16.022 --> 40:19.199
I've accepted a job
with the Englishman, Tunstall.

40:23.856 --> 40:26.728
I'm leaving today.

40:26.859 --> 40:29.688
[tense music plays]

40:29.818 --> 40:32.604
♪♪♪

40:35.563 --> 40:36.869
Well, you are a little piece
of shit, ain't you?

40:36.999 --> 40:39.872
Huh.

40:40.002 --> 40:42.091
What'd I say? Hmm?

40:44.442 --> 40:47.836
Billy, I'm your oldest friend.

40:47.967 --> 40:50.273
We've ridden together
a long time.

40:50.404 --> 40:52.580
We had some good times,
we had some bad times,

40:52.711 --> 40:53.581
but our friendship...

40:53.712 --> 40:56.758
has always remained.

41:00.588 --> 41:05.114
I can't believe that
you're gonna quit on me now.

41:05.245 --> 41:07.595
It don't make any sense.

41:07.726 --> 41:10.685
I'm sorry, Jesse.

41:10.816 --> 41:12.992
This wasn't an easy decision
to make.

41:13.122 --> 41:14.689
I've made up my mind.

41:14.820 --> 41:17.431
Yeah.

41:17.562 --> 41:19.999
That you're a traitor
and our enemy.

41:23.176 --> 41:25.613
I just came here
to tell you in person.

41:27.223 --> 41:30.836
Some of us have been friends.

41:30.966 --> 41:33.055
When this is all done,
we can be friends again.

41:33.186 --> 41:34.709
Is that what you're hoping?

41:34.840 --> 41:38.974
That we're gonna be friends?
[laughs]

41:40.062 --> 41:43.152
[groans]

41:43.283 --> 41:45.372
[hammers clicking]

41:45.503 --> 41:46.895
Do you really think we're just
gonna let you leave?

41:47.026 --> 41:50.333
-After what you've just done?
-Boys, boys.

41:50.464 --> 41:53.685
We've all slept, starved,

41:53.815 --> 41:56.905
fought with The Kid.

41:57.036 --> 42:00.735
See, he's trusted himself
amongst us.

42:00.866 --> 42:03.956
He didn't sneak out.

42:04.086 --> 42:07.046
He came right out and told us.

42:07.176 --> 42:10.005
Let him go his way.

42:10.136 --> 42:12.573
Our time will come.

42:17.143 --> 42:20.625
Yeah. It will.

42:25.978 --> 42:28.023
Yah! Yah, yah!

42:30.286 --> 42:31.853
Chickenshit.

42:31.984 --> 42:34.813
♪♪♪

42:40.732 --> 42:43.169
[Billy] My family came
to America on the promise

42:43.299 --> 42:46.346
of just and fair treatment
for all.

42:48.870 --> 42:52.004
I wanna believe that promise.

42:52.134 --> 42:54.963
♪♪♪
